<item>
<title>[HHR-121] Policy AI UI Changes</title>
<link>https://coralshades.atlassian.net/browse/HHR-121</link>
<project id="10004" key="HHR">HH Policy AI</project>
<description><p>Enhance the Policy AI UI based on feedback to improve visual clarity, usability, and alignment with design expectations. The changes relate to the existing Policy AI screen and are primarily cosmetic. Screenshots of the proposed changes will be attached to this ticket.</p> <hr /> <h3><a name="Scope%2FRequirements"></a><b>Scope / Requirements</b></h3> <ol> <li><b>Remove Welcome Block</b> <ul> <li>Remove the current welcome/instruction block from the top of the page.</li> <li>Ensure layout adjusts cleanly once removed (no excessive white space).</li> </ul> </li> </ol> <p><span class="image-wrap" style=""><img src="/rest/api/3/attachment/content/10274" alt="image-20251107-085414.png" width="667" style="border: 0px solid black" /></span></p> <ol> <li><b>Update Header Styling</b> <ul> <li>Apply coloured header styling (matching the visual style example from WorkflowMax).</li> <li>Add darker shading variations to create visual hierarchy and separation.</li> </ul> </li> </ol> <p><span class="image-wrap" style=""><img src="/rest/api/3/attachment/content/10272" alt="image-20251107-090918.png" width="667" style="border: 0px solid black" /></span></p> <ol> <li><b>Add Border Around Table(Try this and see how it looks, if no good keep as is)</b> <ul> <li>Apply a visible border around the entire table area.</li> <li>Ensure the border aligns with the header styling for a consistent look.</li> </ul> </li> </ol> <p><span class="image-wrap" style=""><img src="/rest/api/3/attachment/content/10275" alt="image-20251107-085513.png" width="667" style="border: 0px solid black" /></span></p> <ol> <li><b>Highlight Table Header Row (Grey Background - Try this and see how it looks, if no good keep as is)</b> <ul> <li>Add a grey background to the table header row to differentiate it from table rows.</li> <li>Ensure text contrast is accessible (WCAG compliant where possible).</li> </ul> </li> </ol> <p><span class="image-wrap" style=""><img src="/rest/api/3/attachment/content/10273" alt="image-20251107-090857.png" width="667" style="border: 0px solid black" /></span></p></description>
